OL,4,Cdriver jailed for life
OL,6,FThe court heard witnesses heard Mr
OL,7,FKondor shouting for help, fearing for
OL,8,Fhis life.
OL,10,FProsecutors said the defendant was
OL,11,Ftrying to "get rid" of Mr Kondor.
OL,13,FRoss hit two stationary cars, causing
OL,14,FMr Kondor unsurvivable head and chest
OL,15,Finjuries.
OL,17,FHe admitted manslaughter but denied
OL,18,Fmurdering Mr Kondor, claiming he was
OL,19,Funaware he was holding on. He was
OL,20,Ffound guilty after around a day of
OL,21,Fjury deliberations.
